{
  "stem": "9943.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a completely-- a complete difference.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I then was close to six years old.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then, then they-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then they started to, to teach us Russian in the school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So came first to a-- to a school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We worked with-- the teacher asked me my name.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I said Brandla.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she said, why don't we call you Berta?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's how gradually my name from Brandla became Berta and afterwards became Alberta.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, 'Brein-de-lah.'",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's how they called me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in-- in this little town, the life was kosher, a Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yiddish was spoken all around.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Except my parents, with each other, they spoke Russian.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother finished gymnasium in Luck.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she was educated officially, formally.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In other words, she went to gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father was taught in that-- in that shtetl by teachers, special teachers-- was very well educated, but without going to any school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In, in Rostov, it was where my father was occupied with my brother's education.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother was entrusted with the education of the children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's how my parents agreed to.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother wanted me to go to gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she took me one day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was going to a school where they was teaching me Russian-- and write and read.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We took me to gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And at that time, in order to be accepted to the second preparatory school before the first class of gymnasium, you have to-- you had to know this.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It means Russian words that were used in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH], that is now not used anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "After the Revolution, it was changed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But you had to know a list of words.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
